messages.message: Hi team, just wanted to check, for generating protos, I can see the go files are changed when running `go generate instabase/protos/...`. Do we still need to run `cd ~/instabase/webserver/api-server/ && poetry run make build-protos` to generate the corresponding python files?
make build-protos regenerates all protos now (go, Python, JS)
qq should we still be in poetry env for this? I tend to always run `poetry shell` before running any make commands but wonder if it's still necessary
